         </step>
      </steps-unordered>
      <postreq class="- topic/section task/postreq ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Not all transaction data loaded in the system is qualified to be used in calculating the qualification amount and benefit amount.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The following filtering logic applies:</p>
         <ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Filtered by program dates:</uicontrol> If the transaction line is of type Order Line Item, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Pricing Date</uicontrol> of the order line item must fall between the program start date and end date.</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Filtered by filters specified in program scope</uicontrol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Filtered by-products included and excluded: </uicontrol>
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">If the program definition has categories defined, filtered by products that are part of the category.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Filtering logic is independent among programs, which means one transaction line can be potentially bucketed into multiple payout schedules and be counted more than once.</li>
               </ul>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p class="- topic/p ">New "Type" field value for the Q&amp;B page_CIM441 (It is applicable for MEB, RSP, PKG, BUNDLE, PRSP) </p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Add a new value "Product Group" if the benefit line is for a product group</li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">Change CPG type to be "CPG". It is "All" in R1.</li>
         </ol>
      </postreq>
